Beautiful and sunny- thick weeds (some type of milfoil) makes motoring difficult if not impossible- algae growth also present.
Increasing clouds- warm + humid- some algae clinging to weeds.

Sunny- no clouds- breezy.  Eurasian water milfoil and coontail still a major problem- slightly less dense than previous trip but still forms a thick mat in the middle of the lake- around the perimeter as well- but not as thick.
Nice sunny day- few clouds- birds out- divers- crows- turkey vultures on the fields- many fishermen- oaks greening after leafout- weed growth starting not yet in full force.
Biggest difference compared to last year is no huge weed matter in the middle of the lake- can motor easily
Warm and 85 degrees- lake dropped 8" in the last week or so.
1 METER BELOW SURFACE AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH
4" of rain in the previous week.
RUN SP EVEN IF HOLDING TIME EXCEEDED
Weedy at surface- 76 deg F. Cloudy- no wind
Algal bloom- very windy- 80 deg F. Mostly sunny. No wind- humid. Sampled in deeper location than last time.
Algae bloom to north side of lake. 80 deg F. 5-8 mph west wind. Partly sunny. Cumulonimbus clouds. Syringe broken- no D.O.
Sunny- hazy- partly clouds. W wind 10-12 mph. 90 deg F. Large algal mats on lake.
Partly sunny- hazy. 78 deg F. E wind 5-8 mph. Humid. Fish and clam die-off- mostly fish- cause unknown.
Sunny- few high cirrus clouds. NNW wind 15-20 mph. 61 deg F. Not as much algae. Plants less too. Water near shore seems clearer.

column2: sunny- litte breeze- nice day to be out on lake- but water is very murky
the sky was overcast- rain is again expected--this prevented me from monitoring sooner.  Lake was murky + dirty
sunny weather--pleasant day with some breeze
windy- waves-- sunny- chilly--no visible plant growth--water very turbid
sunny--working with Michelle Harrison--lake is very quiet- very little wind--a couple of people fishing in rowboats--lake looks turbid--air temp 60.8 F

new volunteers John + Nancy Konkel along--Secchi disk reading today was the highest I've ever gotten on Mason Lake in the nearly 13 years I've been testing the lake--could see the bottom in many places- where there were either no aquatic plants or very few--slightly breezy- sunny- upper 70s--a few boats out on the lake- but lake wasn't busy
air temp in mid 40s--one fishing boat out--no aquatic plant growth noted
